[1mNAME[0m[m
       date - print or set the system date and time[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mdate [22m[[4mOPTION[24m]... [[4m+FORMAT[24m][m
       [1mdate [22m[[4m-u|--utc|--universal[24m] [[4mMMDDhhmm[24m[[[4mCC[24m][4mYY[24m][[4m.ss[24m]][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       Display the current time in the given FORMAT, or set the system date.[m
[m
       [1m-d[22m, [1m--date[22m=[4mSTRING[0m[m
              display time described by STRING, not `now'[m
[m
       [1m-f[22m, [1m--file[22m=[4mDATEFILE[0m[m
              like [1m--date [22monce for each line of DATEFILE[m
[m
       [1m-r[22m, [1m--reference[22m=[4mFILE[0m[m
              display the last modification time of FILE[m
[m
       [1m-R[22m, [1m--rfc-2822[0m[m
              output  date  and time in RFC 2822 format.  Example: Mon, 07 Aug[m
              2006 12:34:56 [1m-0600[0m[m
[m
       [1m--rfc-3339[22m=[4mTIMESPEC[0m[m
              output date and time in RFC 3339 format.  TIMESPEC=`date', `sec-[m
              onds',  or  `ns'  for  date and time to the indicated precision.[m
              Date and time  components  are  separated  by  a  single  space:[m
              2006-08-07 12:34:56-06:00[m
[m
       [1m-s[22m, [1m--set[22m=[4mSTRING[0m[m
              set time described by STRING[m
[m
       [1m-u[22m, [1m--utc[22m, [1m--universal[0m[m
              print or set Coordinated Universal Time[m
[m
       [1m--help [22mdisplay this help and exit[m
[m
       [1m--version[0m[m
              output version information and exit[m
[m
       FORMAT controls the output.  Interpreted sequences are:[m
[m
       %%     a literal %[m
